title: For Sale:  Mort Kuntsler Civil War Tribute Rifle - Limited Edition from America Remembers
postcontent:
Mort Kunstler Civil War Tribute Rifle - Each Tribute rifle is decorated by craftsmen specifically commissioned by America Remembers And was limited edition of only 300 museum quality pieces. This beautifuly crafted rifle is based on the famous Henry Rifle (which is now perfectly reproduced by the Uberti company), it's barrel Length is 24 1/4" and is .44-40 Caliber. This is a 100% working and firing rifle. This has been in a climate control storage facility it has never been handled without gloves, the action has never been cycled, nor has the hammer been cocked or the trigger pulled. It comes in the original case with orignal pacakaging and the COA. Perfect and rare piece by the famed Mort Kunstler. I also have 5 limited edition autographed prints framed for sale if you want to add civil war pictures in the room this will be so proudly displayed. Also included is an original custom display case built specifically for this rifle.

Mort Kunstler - Left Side

Right side showcases a Künstler favorite, "Chamberlain's Charge," as Joshua Chamberlain leads Union forces at Gettysburg in the famed bayonet charge against the attacking Confederate forces.  To the right, Lee and Jackson are shown on horseback in "...They Were Soldiers Indeed."   To the far left is one of Künstler's earliest Civil War paintings titled, "War Between the States," as a Union soldier drinks from his canteen.  The Künstler images are framed by a 24-karat gold decorated background with elegant scrollwork.  Craftsmen commissioned specifically for this Tribute by America Remembers capture Mr. Künstler's original artwork in minute detail, with a nickel background serving as the canvas for the artwork.

Mort Kunstler - Right Side

Left side of receiver features Robert E. Lee and Thomas "Stonewall" Jackson inspecting J.E.B. Stuart's cavalry troops in "Review at Moss Neck."  To the left, "The High Tide" features Pickett's Charge at Gettysburg.  Confederate forces briefly broke through the Union line, but were eventually turned back.  For many, this historic moment represents a turning point for the Confederate forces.  To the far right, a Confederate soldier pauses for water in "Still Flying," a companion piece to "War Between the States," which is featured on the right side.

Mort Kunstler - Stock 	The hand polished walnut stocks are laser-carved with Mort Künstler's signature on both sides.

postcontent:
AR-10, 7.62x51mm (.308 Win) New in the box, never fired, never a round chambered, never a scope mounted on it.  LWRCI REPR with 20 inch barrel in the box with a 20 round PMAG, which came with it, plus box and instruction manual. 

The LWRCI REPR is noted for having the best gas piston system available on the market, worldwide.  It has long range capability with superb "tested" accuracy according to the detailed rifle report in Shotgun News where the shooter/tester got 0.3 MOA using Hornady Match ammo and a Nightforce 5.5-22x56mm scope.   You can't get much better than that. 0.3 MOA is about the size of your pinky fingernail. Putting 5 shots in a group like that is precision indeed, hence what REPR stands for: Rapid Engagement Precision Rifle. 

The rifle is also of the highest quality billet construction, and it comes standard with a fully adjustable 2 Stage Gesseille National Match Trigger to suit your needs, and has the infamous Left Side Charging handle that is non-reciprocating: that means when the bolt opens the charging handle stays put, so there is no way it can come back and slam your hand/break your finger such as the SCAR does. Also featured is the Magpul PRS fully adjustable buttstock for comb height and length of pull. Notice in the pictures of the rifle below that I have it extended back some. There is room for more adjustment if you desire. Mount it and see.  It's a great feature to have because you can  hand adjust the length of pull according to how much clothing you have one. For example, in cold weather you will be wearing more clothing so you can shorten the length of pull in seconds to fit you perfectly. In warm weather you would adjust it out to a longer length of pull because you might be wearing just a thin Tshirt.  

The rifle comes with the highest quality back up iron sights, which are made by LWRCI.  LWRCI's are known for their reliability and feeding/ejecting without jamming in very bad conditions, such as dunking the rifle in water (UTube this) then shooting a full clip, again and again. This is  a top tier quality tactical rifle in all regards and has the accuracy to get to you 1,000 yds and beyond. And you'll get the velocity with the 20 inch barrel. 
I bought the rifle about 5 months ago, and am moving so I am looking to sell.

Great looking Mosin Nagant for sale. Has matching serial numbers throughout (may be force matched in areas by the Russian arsenal) and has a matching bayonet. Please note that there are some blemishes on this gun which is why I am letting go at this price.  There were a few surface rust spots that I had to remove. These blemishes include the bluing on the top of the receiver, some of which was from from the importer and some added by hitting the rust spot with steel wool. (see pic).  There was also a spot of rust on the top of the bolt which was removed (this is also visible on the gun).  The sides and internal workings of the bolt and receiver of the gun do NOT have any rust.  The stock is in great condition and the barrel has not been counter-bored.

Overall this is still a beautiful 30's era rifle and would be enjoyed by anyone that wants to shoot cheap rounds with a reliable and fun gun.

Beretta Nano 9mm

The Beretta Nano is the ultimate evolution of the micro compact carry pistol. Utilizing a removable, serialized sub-chassis the Nano pistol can be easily modified with replaceable grip frames and is simple to disassemble and maintain. Ease of use and concealment were key drivers in the development of the Nano. The Nano’s extremely low profile, snag free design makes it easy to carry and draw from concealment. To accommodate right or left-handed use, the Nano’s magazine release button can be easily reversed. The light, durable, frame employs modern thermoplastic technology through the use of fiberglass reinforced technopolymer. The Nano’s sights are user adjustable with a 1.3mm hexwrench and your fingers. This allows anyone to adjust their sights without the assistance of a gunsmith. Modular structure, ergonomics and ease of use make the Beretta Nano the ideal firearm for concealed carry. Made in The U.S.A.

Features:
The slide and barrel are finished with black nitride, while the internal chassis is stainless steel and major springs are zinc plated.
Like most Beretta pistols, the Nano has a reversible magazine release button. All you need is a small punch and you can easy change it for right or left-handed use.
The Nano’s 3-dot low profile sights are extremely user friendly. All you need is a 1.3 mm hex wrench and you can adjust, remove, and replace the Nano’s sights in seconds.
The stainless steel chassis of the Nano is the part that carries the serial number. The technopolymer grip frame can be easily removed for cleaning or to be replaced by a different grip frame.
Easy to clean, easy to use. All you need to do is press the Striker Deactivator, turn the Disassembly Cam ¼ turn counterclockwise, and the slide pops right off. The recoil spring is captured so it won’t fly away.
The Nano primary mission is concealed carry. It’s smooth, snag free profile makes it easy to holster, easy to carry and easy to draw. No awkward levers or switches to get caught or hung up on.
Designed for the rigors of concealed carry, the Nano's magazine and follower are constructed entirely of polished stainless steel. The polymer floorplate completely covers the bottom of the Nano's gripframe to reduce the introduction of foreign contaminants and create a uniform grip.
Don’t like pulling the trigger to disassemble your handgun? Neither do we. Simply press the Striker Deactivator with a small punch or ball point pen and you can safely deactivate the striker system. It works a lot like the decocker on our military’s M9 pistol.
3 inch barrel
(1) 6 round flush fit AND (1) 8 round extended magazine
factory hard case
Made in the USA
